  <summary>11/9/1999--Introduced.
Urges the President to initiate emergency negotiations with Russia leading to reciprocal reductions in the strategic and substrategic arsenals in both countries. Welcomes House Resolution 82 concerning further nuclear disarmament and requests the support of Congress to promote such measures through the United Nations. Requests that a congressional delegation convene meetings with a delegation from the Russian Duma as soon as possible to discuss such disarmament between both countries.</summary>
